---
title: "Commentary on Two Articles by C. A. Los"
year: 1991
abstract: >
  Recently, C. A. Los has recommended that all previous methods for
  estimating linear relations from data with unknown errors be scrapped,
  and proposes to find an 'exact objective mathematical solution' that
  depends only on the data. We discuss this with the conclusions that
  (1) his criticisms of previous methods, while overly severe, make some
  important points worth noting; (2) however, his solution ignores
  relevant information and does not exist except in very special cases;
  (3) the Los solution, when it exists, may be characterized as the one
  which would be correct if we had an infinite amount of data which led
  to the same data correlation matrix; (4) methods for dealing with the
  problem which are optimal in all cases have been known for 20 years.
author:
["E.T. Jaynes"]
---
